#############################################
		Instructions
#############################################

1. To compile, use the following commands:

$ cmake .
$ make

2. Execution: loading one picture:

$ ./imageLoader picture1.png 

Change picture1.png to the location of the desired picture. For example:

$ ./imageLoader Lenna.png

Where Lenna.png is in the same directory of imageLoader

3. Execution: loading more than one picture:

$ ./imageLoader picture1.png picture2.png [...]

Change picture1.png, picture2.png and so on, to the location of the desired pictures. For example:

$ ./imageLoader Lenna.png Alligator.png

Where Lenna.png and Alligator.png are in the same directory of imageLoader

#############################################

Thanks for reading.
